---
import Container from "@components/Container.astro";
import Footer from "@components/Footer.astro";
import GetAppButton from "@components/GetAppButton.astro";
import Page from "@layouts/Page.astro";
---

<Page
  title="Box Timer – Free HIIT Timer App for iPhone"
  description="Free HIIT interval timer app for iPhone and iPad. Custom work/rest intervals, adjustable rounds, and loud audio cues. No ads, no subscriptions. 4.9 stars."
  url="https://boxtimer.app/hiit-timer/"
  canonical="https://boxtimer.app/hiit-timer/"
>
  <Container innerClass={"flex-col items-center"}>
    <div class="w-full sm:w-9/12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-sans font-bold">
        Free HIIT Timer for iPhone
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl font-light text-zinc-600 mt-4">
        The simple, ad-free interval timer for high-intensity interval training
      </p>

      <div class="flex justify-center mt-12 mb-16">
        <GetAppButton id="get-app-button-hiit-top" />
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-sans font-bold mt-16 mb-4">What is HIIT?</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        HIIT (High-Intensity Interval Training) alternates short bursts of
        intense exercise with recovery periods. A typical HIIT session lasts
        <strong>15 to 30 minutes</strong> and can burn more calories than traditional
        steady-state cardio in less time.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4">
        HIIT works with any exercise: running, cycling, bodyweight movements,
        kettlebells, or gym machines. The key is pushing hard during work
        periods and recovering during rest. A reliable interval timer is
        essential to keep the structure tight.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-sans font-bold mt-16 mb-4">
        Why Box Timer for HIIT?
      </h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-6 space-y-3">
        <li>
          <strong>Flexible intervals</strong> — Set any combination of work time,
          rest time, and rounds. From quick 15-second sprints to longer 45-second
          circuits.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Loud audio cues</strong> — Beeps at every transition so you know
          exactly when to push and when to rest, even with headphones off.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Works with your music</strong> — Keep your workout playlist going.
          Timer sounds mix with your audio instead of cutting it off.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Screen stays on</strong> — The display stays awake during your
          workout so you can always glance at the time remaining.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Workout history</strong> — Sessions are saved automatically. Name
          and pin your go-to HIIT workouts for one-tap reuse.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>No ads, ever</strong> — No interruptions between rounds. No subscriptions.
          No premium tier. Just a timer.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-sans font-bold mt-16 mb-4">
        How to set up a HIIT timer
      </h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-outside ml-6 space-y-2">
        <li>Open Box Timer and tap <strong>Edit Timer</strong></li>
        <li>Select <strong>Interval</strong> as the timer type</li>
        <li>Set <strong>Rounds</strong> to your desired number</li>
        <li>Set <strong>Work</strong> time (e.g. 0 minutes and 30 seconds)</li>
        <li>Set <strong>Rest</strong> time (e.g. 0 minutes and 15 seconds)</li>
        <li>Turn on <strong>Countdown</strong> for a 10-second lead-in</li>
        <li>Tap <strong>Save</strong>, then <strong>Start</strong></li>
      </ol>
      <p class="mt-4">
        See the full guide:
        <a
          class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800"
          href="/support/how-to-set-an-interval-timer-with-both-work-and-rest-time/"
          >How to set an interval timer with both work and rest time</a
        >
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-sans font-bold mt-16 mb-4">
        Popular HIIT formats
      </h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full mt-4">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th class="text-left pb-4 pr-4 font-bold">Format</th>
              <th class="text-left pb-4 pr-4 font-bold">Work</th>
              <th class="text-left pb-4 pr-4 font-bold">Rest</th>
              <th class="text-left pb-4 font-bold">Rounds</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">Classic HIIT</td>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">30s</td>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">30s</td>
              <td class="py-2">10</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">Sprint intervals</td>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">20s</td>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">40s</td>
              <td class="py-2">8</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">Tabata</td>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">20s</td>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">10s</td>
              <td class="py-2">8</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">Circuit training</td>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">45s</td>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">15s</td>
              <td class="py-2">12</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">Beginner HIIT</td>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">20s</td>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">40s</td>
              <td class="py-2">6</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-4 text-zinc-600">
        All of these can be set up in Box Timer using the interval timer mode.
      </p>

      <div class="flex justify-center mt-16 mb-8">
        <GetAppButton id="get-app-button-hiit-bottom" />
      </div>

      <p class="mt-16">
        <strong>Related:</strong>
        <a class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800" href="/tabata-timer/"
          >Free Tabata Timer for iPhone</a
        >
        &nbsp;·&nbsp;
        <a
          class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800"
          href="/2026-best-workout-timers-iphone/"
          >Best Workout Timer Apps for iPhone in 2026</a
        >
      </p>
    </div>
  </Container>
  <Footer />
  <script type="application/ld+json">
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "HowTo",
      "name": "How to set up a HIIT timer on iPhone",
      "step": [
        { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Open Box Timer and tap Edit Timer" },
        { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Select Interval as the timer type" },
        { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Set Rounds to your desired number" },
        { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Set Work time" },
        { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Set Rest time" },
        {
          "@type": "HowToStep",
          "name": "Turn on Countdown for a 10-second lead-in"
        },
        { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Tap Save, then Start" }
      ]
    }
  </script>
</Page>
